Reasoning: The paper deals with analyzing the performance of randomized algorithms on graphs, specifically the cover time and broadcast time of random walks. This falls under the scope of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of random walks in network algorithms, which is relevant to network science (cs.NE). The analysis of the runtime of randomized algorithms involves information theory (cs.IT) and the paper also discusses the relationship between cover time and broadcast time, which falls under the scope of social and information networks (cs.SI).
